1
00:03:28,800 --> 00:03:32,880
-What's that ambulance doing there?
-I don't know. I'll check it out.

2
00:03:48,944 --> 00:03:50,652
-Evening, sir.
-How's it going, Griff?

3
00:03:50,821 --> 00:03:52,897
I can't complain... and won't.

4
00:03:53,240 --> 00:03:54,319
Is that him?

5
00:03:54,867 --> 00:03:58,449
Yep. Might just be some crackpot but
I figured I should call you anyway.

6
00:03:58,620 --> 00:04:00,328
Did he ask for me by name?

7
00:04:00,706 --> 00:04:02,034
Nope, asked for the agent
in charge of

8
00:04:02,165 --> 00:04:05,083
the "God's Hand" case. Said he had
some important info on it.

9
00:04:05,544 --> 00:04:08,710
-Didn't say what?
-Nope. Said he'd only talk to you.

10
00:04:15,804 --> 00:04:17,927
You the agent in charge of
the "God's Hand" case?

11
00:04:18,681 --> 00:04:20,473
That's right.
Wesley Doyle.

12
00:04:22,935 --> 00:04:24,560
That a picture
of you and your mother, huh?

13
00:04:26,189 --> 00:04:29,059
I'd appreciate it if you wouldn't
take things off my desk.

14
00:04:29,942 --> 00:04:31,140
Sorry about that.

15
00:04:31,736 --> 00:04:33,278
Guess I've been in here a while.

16
00:04:34,572 --> 00:04:37,193
Already had a look at all
your plaques and your citations.

17
00:04:38,075 --> 00:04:39,273
Didn't really care
to have a look at those.

18
00:04:46,750 --> 00:04:50,201
What can I do for you, Mr...?

19
00:04:50,379 --> 00:04:51,410
Meiks.

20
00:04:52,005 --> 00:04:53,416
My name's Fenton Meiks.

21
00:04:55,509 --> 00:04:57,916
Now listen, this may sound
a little bit crazy but...

22
00:05:00,805 --> 00:05:03,094
I know who
the "God's Hand" killer is.

23
00:05:04,225 --> 00:05:05,636
All right, I'll bite.

24
00:05:06,728 --> 00:05:07,842
Who?

25
00:05:09,188 --> 00:05:11,940
You haven't even heard me out yet
and already you doubt me.

26
00:05:13,526 --> 00:05:14,724
Why is that?

27
00:05:16,571 --> 00:05:20,153
Because in a case like this
nobody just walks in the office

28
00:05:20,282 --> 00:05:21,942
and tells you who the killer is.
It doesn't happen that way.

29
00:05:23,744 --> 00:05:27,907
-Sometimes truth defies reason.
-Yeah?

30
00:05:28,082 --> 00:05:29,789
So who is it then?

31
00:05:31,585 --> 00:05:32,748
My brother.

32
00:05:34,504 --> 00:05:36,047
What makes you think that?

33
00:05:37,758 --> 00:05:39,715
I got a call from him...

34
00:05:41,219 --> 00:05:42,298
last night.

35
00:05:49,144 --> 00:05:50,389
Hello?

36
00:05:51,271 --> 00:05:54,355
-Hello?
-Demons are taking over the world.

37
00:05:57,026 --> 00:05:58,105
Adam?

38
00:05:58,236 --> 00:05:59,896
I can't destroy them all.

39
00:06:00,196 --> 00:06:04,146
-I can't take it anymore!
-Now, let's talk about this, Adam.

40
00:06:04,283 --> 00:06:06,240
But there's nothing to talk about!

41
00:06:06,827 --> 00:06:09,235
It's over...
whatever happens,

42
00:06:09,788 --> 00:06:14,331
you have to take me to the rose
garden. You promised, remember?

43
00:06:14,918 --> 00:06:16,496
-Now, that's just till...
-Remember?.

44
00:06:16,712 --> 00:06:18,123
You promised!

45
00:06:54,415 --> 00:06:55,577
Meat?

46
00:06:56,166 --> 00:06:58,492
That's where all this took place.

47
00:06:58,669 --> 00:07:01,290
It's about 200 miles west of here,
just north of Abilene.

48
00:07:01,964 --> 00:07:03,422
Why did you go to Thurman?

49
00:07:03,841 --> 00:07:06,166
To bury Adam,
in the rose garden.

50
00:07:06,843 --> 00:07:08,219
Why would you do that?

51
00:07:08,887 --> 00:07:11,592
I promised him I would.
A long time ago.

52
00:07:13,767 --> 00:07:16,258
That's a pretty
wild story, Mr. Meiks.

53
00:07:17,270 --> 00:07:19,891
I don't see what, if anything,
this has got to do with my case.

54
00:07:20,940 --> 00:07:23,562
Adam is the "God's Hand" killer,
Agent Doyle.

55
00:07:25,403 --> 00:07:27,111
He's the one you're looking for.

56
00:07:27,739 --> 00:07:30,989
Did he tell you that before
he asked you to take him to Thurman?

57
00:07:31,784 --> 00:07:33,741
If that's the case,
you left that part out.

58
00:07:33,995 --> 00:07:35,323
I haven't finished yet.

59
00:07:35,538 --> 00:07:37,910
-Oh, there's more?
-A lot more.

60
00:07:40,084 --> 00:07:41,329
Excuse me a minute.

61
00:07:54,681 --> 00:07:56,010
Meat Sheriff's office.

62
00:07:56,183 --> 00:07:59,966
Can I talk to a sheriff, please?
This is Agent Doyle of the FBI.

63
00:08:01,313 --> 00:08:03,601
He's not in right now.
May I help you?

64
00:08:04,399 --> 00:08:06,641
Well, I've got a man here
in my office, name of Fenton Meiks.

65
00:08:06,818 --> 00:08:10,021
Fenton Meiks?
What's he doing there?

66
00:08:11,072 --> 00:08:15,152
-You know him?
-Hecaused a ruckus here earlier.

67
00:08:15,326 --> 00:08:18,410
He stole an ambulance
and his brother's body too.

68
00:08:22,541 --> 00:08:24,083
Did my story check out?

69
00:08:26,670 --> 00:08:27,915
Yeah, it did.

70
00:08:28,088 --> 00:08:30,377
So am I under arrest now?

71
00:08:32,009 --> 00:08:33,503
You damn sure should be.

72
00:08:34,428 --> 00:08:39,303
The sheriff's willing to forget it
if you bring that ambulance back.

73
00:08:40,058 --> 00:08:41,967
Nobody wants to press any charges.

74
00:08:43,478 --> 00:08:47,061
-Well you gotta love small towns.
-Why would you go to all that

75
00:08:47,232 --> 00:08:49,639
trouble just to walk in here
and confess it to me?

76
00:08:50,819 --> 00:08:53,392
I'm here because I can't live
with what I know anymore.

77
00:08:57,867 --> 00:08:59,409
What exactly do you know?

78
00:09:01,954 --> 00:09:03,117
That is your mother, isn't it?

79
00:09:04,624 --> 00:09:06,746
-Yeah, it is.
-I knew it.

80
00:09:07,752 --> 00:09:09,412
You got the same eyes.

81
00:09:10,087 --> 00:09:11,878
Why don't we
get back to your story?

82
00:09:13,424 --> 00:09:14,538
What makes you think

83
00:09:14,717 --> 00:09:16,590
that your brother's
the "God's Hand" killer?

84
00:09:17,511 --> 00:09:19,005
I know it was him.

85
00:09:19,721 --> 00:09:20,966
How do you know?

86
00:09:22,307 --> 00:09:24,929
It started back in Thurman.

87
